1
00:01:14,279 --> 00:01:15,080
Hey, darling.

2
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:16,040
How are you feeling today?

3
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:17,639
Don't even mention it.

4
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:18,639
I drank too much last night.

5
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,040
I don't even know how I got back.

6
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:22,199
You can't keep doing this.

7
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,639
What if you ran into bad guys on the way?

8
00:01:25,839 --> 00:01:27,199
It's not that serious.

9
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:28,720
But seriously,

10
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,680
I felt like I saw someone last night.

11
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,239
But I can't remember who it was.

12
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,120
You should think hard about it.

13
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:36,199
Make sure nothing actually happened last night.

14
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:37,760
What could possibly happen?

15
00:01:38,199 --> 00:01:38,919
Forget it, I won't think about it.

16
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:39,919
I can't remember anyway.

17
00:01:40,319 --> 00:01:41,000
All right, all right.

18
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:42,040
Don't think about it anymore.

19
00:01:42,839 --> 00:01:43,680
Today,

20
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,879
just drink some warm water to soothe your stomach.

21
00:01:46,879 --> 00:01:47,319
I know.

22
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,040
What did you say?

23
00:01:49,839 --> 00:01:50,839
What do you mean Flair has already

24
00:01:50,839 --> 00:01:51,839
signed with Zhenyang Department Store?

25
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,199
I heard they already finished signing yesterday.

26
00:01:54,519 --> 00:01:56,160
If anyone's to blame, it's that Traitor, Secretary Lin.

27
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,319
If it weren't for her

28
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,760
accompanying our competitor,

29
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,639
how could they sign so quickly?

30
00:02:01,319 --> 00:02:03,400
What an ungrateful wretch.

31
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:07,000
How dare she do such a thing.

32
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,800
Where is she now?

33
00:02:13,919 --> 00:02:14,559
Hello, President Gu.

34
00:02:17,279 --> 00:02:18,360
Print this for me.

35
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,160
Okay.

36
00:02:19,479 --> 00:02:19,919
Hello.

37
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,000
Which way to the conference room?

38
00:02:21,199 --> 00:02:21,839
Over there.

39
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:23,399
Director Feng.

40
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,520
Why didn't you say hello when you saw me?

41
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:29,399
Gu Tiancheng.

42
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,520
I'm already trying hard not to curse at you.

43
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,960
And you still want me to say hello?

44
00:02:36,839 --> 00:02:38,080
I am your boss.

45
00:02:39,399 --> 00:02:40,679
Is this how you talk to your boss?

46
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,039
What did I tell you before?

47
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,559
I asked you to take good care of Lin Jiaqi.

48
00:02:46,399 --> 00:02:47,160
And look at what happened now.

49
00:02:47,679 --> 00:02:48,399
Your so-called taking care of her

50
00:02:48,639 --> 00:02:50,039
is letting her suffer this kind of treatment.

51
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:51,800
If you have any dissatisfaction with me,

52
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:52,720
come at me.

53
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,080
Don't bully her.

54
00:02:54,559 --> 00:02:55,800
You've been yelling for a while, and I still don't get it.

55
00:02:56,399 --> 00:02:57,199
What happened to Lin Jiaqi?

56
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,240
Stop playing dumb with me.

57
00:02:59,119 --> 00:03:00,279
If Jiaqi does something foolish because of this,

58
00:03:01,119 --> 00:03:02,039
I won't let you off.

59
00:03:07,399 --> 00:03:08,000
Jiaqi.

60
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,360
I was looking for you.

61
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:11,520
How are you?

62
00:03:14,559 --> 00:03:15,160
I'm fine.

63
00:03:16,199 --> 00:03:17,279
Who did this to you?

64
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,240
Was it Gu Tiancheng?

65
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:19,399
Ziang.

66
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,240
Forget it.

67
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,479
Lin Jiaqi.

68
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,160
Chairman.

69
00:03:30,119 --> 00:03:30,800
Traitor.

70
00:03:30,839 --> 00:03:31,440
Jiaqi.

71
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:38,800
Jiaqi.

72
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:39,960
You

73
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,119
are someone I watched

74
00:03:41,199 --> 00:03:42,160
grow up since you were little.

75
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:44,240
From a little girl who knew nothing,

76
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,119
you've come this far relying on my power.

77
00:03:46,279 --> 00:03:47,039
Now your wings are fully fledged,

78
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,520
and you actually use this method against me.

79
00:03:48,839 --> 00:03:50,080
You really don't take me seriously at all.

80
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:50,759
Chairman.

81
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,119
It's not like that.

82
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:53,360
Let's go.

83
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:56,360
Jiaqi.

84
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:57,360
Are you okay?

85
00:04:04,639 --> 00:04:05,360
I'm fine.

86
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,000
All right.

87
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:07,559
There's no one here anymore.

88
00:04:08,199 --> 00:04:08,639
Jiaqi.

89
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:09,759
What exactly happened?

90
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,880
What did the Chairman misunderstand about you?

91
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,199
I thought Gu Tiancheng was making things difficult for you.

92
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,239
Now it seems there's more to it.

93
00:04:16,799 --> 00:04:17,519
Tell me.

94
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,959
I'll help you explain it to the Chairman.

95
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:20,239
There's no need to explain.

96
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,279
I can't explain it clearly in a few words.

97
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:24,920
All right, Ziang.

98
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,600
You should go back now.

99
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:15,519
Senior

100
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,160
After checking all the vehicles,

101
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,239
what did you find?

102
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,519
Look at this.

103
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,640
As of right now,

104
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,359
there's something wrong with this car.

105
00:05:21,679 --> 00:05:22,239
What's wrong with it?

106
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,519
The owner of this car

107
00:05:23,519 --> 00:05:24,440
is Tan Feng's wife.

108
00:05:24,799 --> 00:05:25,399
Who's Tan Feng?

109
00:05:25,519 --> 00:05:26,799
He's the section chief in charge of raw materials.

110
00:05:26,799 --> 00:05:28,399
After the incident, both he and the car disappeared.

111
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,760
But in the last few days,

112
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,600
this car

113
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:31,679
suddenly reappeared.

114
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,239
Is this car in

115
00:05:34,799 --> 00:05:35,920
Tianxin Community?

116
00:05:36,799 --> 00:05:37,600
How did you know?

117
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,000
It really wasn't a simple

118
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,720
hit-and-run.

119
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:40,519
Let's go.

120
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,119
Senior!

121
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:42,480
Senior, wait for me!

122
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,079
Honey,

123
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:49,679
you should go back.

124
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:50,359
I'm leaving.

125
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,239
Don't forget to take your medicine.

126
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,480
Why are we at Tianxin Community?

127
00:05:57,679 --> 00:05:59,239
To catch the suspect, why else?

128
00:06:00,239 --> 00:06:02,079
We've only confirmed the owner's identity.

129
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,839
We can't be sure he's the suspect.

130
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,399
Aren't you just alerting the enemy?

131
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,880
As long as he dares to drive the car back,

132
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:11,119
I'll definitely find evidence in it.

133
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,079
Brilliant.

134
00:06:12,679 --> 00:06:13,959
Keep your eyes peeled.

135
00:06:14,359 --> 00:06:15,359
Watch the license plates closely.

136
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,200
Got it.

137
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,000
Here.

138
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,200
The property deed.

139
00:06:44,839 --> 00:06:45,320
No,

140
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:46,480
who are you trying to prove a point to?

141
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:48,279
Why did you insist on buying this place?

142
00:06:48,679 --> 00:06:50,320
The old lady had already agreed to sell it to someone else.

143
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,679
Why would she sell it to you?

144
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,480
She didn't lose out.

145
00:06:55,559 --> 00:06:56,839
I paid her double the price.

146
00:06:57,359 --> 00:06:58,079
Wrong.

147
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,279
She's lived here almost her whole life.

148
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,959
Did you think money could just solve it?

149
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,359
It's because of me.

150
00:07:03,559 --> 00:07:05,000
Because of my silver tongue.

151
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,119
I told the old lady,

152
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:06,959
I said,

153
00:07:07,079 --> 00:07:07,839
I said you were sick.

154
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:08,519
And then?

155
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:09,600
You'd only find peace living here.

156
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,600
Only here would feel like home.

157
00:07:11,119 --> 00:07:12,200
After a lot of persuading,

158
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,040
she finally sold it to you.

159
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:18,679
Wait.

160
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:22,279
I just said you were sick,

161
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,559
and you actually

162
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:24,799
didn't scold me.

163
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,600
I am sick, after all.

164
00:07:31,399 --> 00:07:32,239
No, no, no.

165
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:33,239
No, no, no.

166
00:07:33,679 --> 00:07:35,119
You're acting really strange today.

167
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:37,160
What's wrong with you?

168
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,079
What's going on with you?

169
00:07:44,559 --> 00:07:45,720
I don't know what's wrong either.

170
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,000
Whenever I walk into this courtyard,

171
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
I feel weird.

172
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:53,399
I always feel like

173
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,440
something is missing.

174
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:33,559
Hello.

175
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,640
How can I help you?

176
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,119
What did I tell you?

177
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,599
If he really had anything to do with the case,

178
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:47,440
there's no way

179
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,799
he'd drive back so blatantly.

180
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,840
Even if there's only a glimmer of hope,

181
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:52,760
I have to try.

182
00:08:53,919 --> 00:08:54,559
Senior.

183
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,719
I know you can't let go

184
00:08:56,719 --> 00:08:57,840
of your childhood friend's case,

185
00:08:57,919 --> 00:08:59,320
but you can't just act so recklessly.

186
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:00,919
If you keep this up,

187
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,159
before you even find the guy,

188
00:09:02,919 --> 00:09:03,840
you'll wear yourself out.

189
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:04,679
What are you talking about?

190
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:06,039
This case clearly has suspicious points.

191
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,599
Even if he wasn't my childhood friend,

192
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,719
or my best friend's boyfriend,

193
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,159
as police officers,

194
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:14,239
we must unconditionally seek the truth.

195
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,919
And then there's Jiaqi.

196
00:09:16,559 --> 00:09:17,039
You have no idea

197
00:09:17,039 --> 00:09:18,200
how much it hurts me

198
00:09:18,679 --> 00:09:19,880
to see her like that every day.

199
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:21,039
Even though

200
00:09:21,039 --> 00:09:22,080
finding the killer

201
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:23,559
won't give her much comfort,

202
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,000
at the very least,

203
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,080
we need to know how Du Zheng died.

204
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:29,159
We haven't found anything here.

205
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:31,320
Why don't we pull out for now?

206
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,280
Let's call it a day.

207
00:09:42,159 --> 00:09:43,359
Hello.

208
00:09:43,599 --> 00:09:44,840
Is this Miss Lin Jiaqi?

209
00:09:45,479 --> 00:09:46,039
Speaking.

210
00:09:46,359 --> 00:09:47,520
This is the Pumpkin Club.

211
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:49,200
Pumpkin Club?

212
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,200
I'm calling for a follow-up

213
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:53,640
to ask if you're satisfied with the ring.

214
00:09:54,119 --> 00:09:54,960
What ring?

215
00:09:55,559 --> 00:09:57,599
Your wedding ring with Mr. Du.

216
00:09:58,479 --> 00:09:59,479
Wedding ring?

217
00:09:59,719 --> 00:10:00,200
Yes.

218
00:10:00,599 --> 00:10:01,640
Your friend came by earlier

219
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,679
and picked it up for you.

220
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:03,919
This is the address he left.

221
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:07,400
Thank you, sir.

222
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:15,559
Is anyone here?

223
00:10:18,799 --> 00:10:19,520
Is anyone here?

224
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:25,840
Look, Jiaqi.

225
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,039
Isn't this exactly

226
00:10:27,039 --> 00:10:28,200
the kind of house you like best?

227
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,119
Tell me,

228
00:10:35,559 --> 00:10:37,000
what kind of flowers should we plant

229
00:10:37,159 --> 00:10:38,400
in this yard in the future?

230
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:41,640
How about crabapple blossoms?

231
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:42,719
Sure.

232
00:10:43,039 --> 00:10:44,119
I love crabapple blossoms the most.

233
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:46,359
Is anyone here?

234
00:10:46,359 --> 00:10:47,119
Jiaqi,

235
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:49,400
we will definitely be very happy.

236
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:50,559
Is anyone here?

237
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:54,960
Who are you looking for?

238
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,200
Why are you here?

239
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:10,280
This is my home.

240
00:11:10,799 --> 00:11:11,799
Where else would I be?

241
00:11:12,799 --> 00:11:13,520
Your home?

242
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:16,799
I remember before,

243
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,400
an auntie lived here.

244
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,359
That auntie sold the house to me.

245
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:22,599
I just moved in.

246
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:24,799
Why did you move here?

247
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:28,520
I can move wherever I want.

248
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,239
Do I need your approval?

249
00:11:33,239 --> 00:11:33,880
Who are you?

250
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,599
Are you crazy?

251
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,039
Asking such a weird question.

252
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,440
Who exactly are you?

253
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,559
I think you really are crazy.

254
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:46,200
I'm Gu Tiancheng.

255
00:11:46,919 --> 00:11:47,760
Who else could I be?

256
00:11:49,359 --> 00:11:50,039
Don't go.

257
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,000
Explain yourself clearly.

258
00:11:52,919 --> 00:11:53,760
Who exactly are you?

259
00:11:54,159 --> 00:11:55,359
Why did you buy a house here?

260
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,000
I liked it here, so I bought it.

261
00:11:58,640 --> 00:11:59,159
What's wrong?

262
00:12:00,559 --> 00:12:01,719
Then when I was injured,

263
00:12:02,559 --> 00:12:03,760
why did you shed tears?

264
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:06,599
I shed tears

265
00:12:06,599 --> 00:12:08,400
because I just had heart surgery.

266
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,520
I'm emotionally unstable.

267
00:12:10,559 --> 00:12:11,760
What about the ring?

268
00:12:13,919 --> 00:12:15,280
Someone picked up my ring.

269
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:16,719
I didn't even know about the ring.

270
00:12:16,719 --> 00:12:17,840
Why would you know?

271
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:19,280
Wait a minute.

272
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,039
Don't get so emotional.

273
00:12:22,119 --> 00:12:23,080
Here's the thing about the ring.

274
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,359
The ring...

275
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,880
That's because I happened

276
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:27,799
to have work

277
00:12:27,799 --> 00:12:29,440
and needed to check the company's store.

278
00:12:30,159 --> 00:12:30,559
As a result,

279
00:12:30,559 --> 00:12:32,080
I found this pick-up slip.

280
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,599
Later, when I opened it,

281
00:12:34,119 --> 00:12:34,799
I found out

282
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:36,320
it was a receipt for a wedding ring.

283
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:38,000
So I kindly picked it up for you.

284
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:39,760
Aren't you going to say thank you?

285
00:12:42,039 --> 00:12:42,880
Is that really true?

286
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,280
What else?

287
00:12:48,479 --> 00:12:49,119
I'm sorry.

288
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:50,640
I made a mistake.

289
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,039
Wait.

290
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:57,520
You got dumped?

291
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,159
Could it be that Curly

292
00:13:01,159 --> 00:13:01,719
suddenly backed out of the wedding

293
00:13:01,719 --> 00:13:02,599
and dumped you?

294
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:08,880
The first time I saw him,

295
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:10,320
I thought he was unreliable.

296
00:13:10,919 --> 00:13:11,719
This kind of person,

297
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:12,559
he should...

298
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,359
Enough.

299
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:18,799
Give me my ring.

300
00:13:20,039 --> 00:13:21,080
Why so fierce?

301
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,000
Give the ring back to me.

302
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:26,280
Fine.

303
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:40,559
You...

304
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:42,280
Does your face still hurt from the slap?

305
00:13:43,919 --> 00:13:44,559
Thank you.

306
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,239
I didn't expect

307
00:14:08,479 --> 00:14:09,200
you actually bought

308
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,840
such a beautiful ring for me.

309
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,880
I thought you'd propose empty-handed.

310
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,119
How about we throw Sister Jiaqi

311
00:14:26,119 --> 00:14:27,280
a farewell party?

312
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:27,919
Sure.

313
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:29,559
After all, we've worked together so long.

314
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:30,520
When leaving,

315
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:31,599
she should be happy.

316
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:32,679
Right.

317
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:34,200
Let's throw a farewell party.

318
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,640
Sister Jiaqi,

319
00:14:37,119 --> 00:14:38,280
but what about you?

320
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,760
I think President Gu means

321
00:14:40,159 --> 00:14:41,559
to really fire you.

322
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,159
President Gu.

323
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:46,400
You're all here.

324
00:14:47,679 --> 00:14:48,400
Secretary Lin is here too.

325
00:14:50,719 --> 00:14:51,320
I'll get going.

326
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,320
Stop right there.

327
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:54,719
Did I let you go?

328
00:14:58,280 --> 00:14:59,440
We'll leave first.

329
00:15:02,799 --> 00:15:04,119
I'm no longer your secretary.

330
00:15:04,719 --> 00:15:05,599
I am your boss.

331
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:06,960
I haven't fired you,

332
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,039
so why are you resigning?

333
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,280
Now the company wants to fire me,

334
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,000
so I can leave.

335
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:12,559
Excuse me.

336
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:25,239
Tiancheng.

337
00:15:26,239 --> 00:15:27,919
You brought this traitor to see me.

338
00:15:28,679 --> 00:15:30,239
Are you trying to provoke me on purpose?

339
00:15:34,799 --> 00:15:36,159
I had someone copy the surveillance footage.

340
00:15:37,239 --> 00:15:38,039
Right and wrong,

341
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:39,760
you can see for yourself.

342
00:15:40,479 --> 00:15:41,640
Lin Jiaqi was framed.

343
00:15:42,159 --> 00:15:43,239
You were deceived

344
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:44,719
by the dog beside you.

345
00:15:47,159 --> 00:15:48,840
Do I need to expose it myself,

346
00:15:49,359 --> 00:15:50,159
Director Hu?

347
00:15:51,679 --> 00:15:52,320
Director Hu,

348
00:15:54,159 --> 00:15:55,200
is this true?

349
00:15:55,719 --> 00:15:56,239
Chairman.

350
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:58,840
Fine.

351
00:16:00,599 --> 00:16:01,760
Even if I misunderstood,

352
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,080
I still don't understand

353
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,119
your actions.

354
00:16:08,239 --> 00:16:09,280
Since Secretary Lin

355
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,960
didn't betray Feimanchi,

356
00:16:11,159 --> 00:16:11,799
that means

357
00:16:11,799 --> 00:16:13,080
she didn't help you out.

358
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,239
Then you should be blaming her.

359
00:16:14,679 --> 00:16:16,520
Why did you bring her here instead,

360
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:18,679
hoping I'd clear her name

361
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:19,599
and reinstate her?

362
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,320
Isn't that too strange?

363
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,440
Anyway, I have the final say on personnel.

364
00:16:37,239 --> 00:16:38,719
Rather than picking someone else to be by my side,

365
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,200
I'd prefer Secretary Lin.

366
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:54,400
Alright.

367
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:55,880
You don't have to thank me too much.

368
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:57,679
Hurry back to your post

369
00:16:57,679 --> 00:16:58,400
and get to work.

370
00:16:59,799 --> 00:17:01,080
You're being way too presumptuous.

371
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:05,000
Do you think I want to?

372
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:07,800
You can't handle your own affairs,

373
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,400
making others worry about you for nothing.

374
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:13,959
You don't need to worry about me.

375
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:16,640
Right.

376
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,560
I just have nothing better to do.

377
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,359
Why does seeing your situation

378
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,359
feel like a fishbone stuck in my throat,

379
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:23,599
an eyelash in my eye,

380
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,400
or shredded squid stuck in my teeth?

381
00:17:30,439 --> 00:17:31,079
Lin Jiaqi,

382
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,599
I know you hate me right now,

383
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,359
but at least I can save your job.

384
00:17:40,599 --> 00:17:41,280
I have one condition.

385
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:46,280
You're negotiating terms with me?

386
00:17:47,319 --> 00:17:49,040
You've got some nerve, Lin Jiaqi.

387
00:17:53,599 --> 00:17:54,239
Just one.

388
00:17:55,119 --> 00:17:55,839
No matter what,

389
00:17:56,599 --> 00:17:58,319
I will never do anything to betray the company.

390
00:17:59,079 --> 00:17:59,800
You don't have to force me.

391
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:00,959
That's it?

392
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:02,560
That's it.

393
00:18:08,319 --> 00:18:08,959
I promise you.

394
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:27,479
The foundation you're using doesn't really suit you.

395
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:28,479
Look.

396
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:29,920
Your pores are very fine,

397
00:18:30,239 --> 00:18:30,719
right?

398
00:18:31,079 --> 00:18:31,680
And also,

399
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,760
there's nothing that needs concealing.

400
00:18:34,359 --> 00:18:34,959
Wait a second.

401
00:18:36,439 --> 00:18:38,000
This one should suit you well.

402
00:18:38,439 --> 00:18:39,160
This one.

403
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:40,239
Try it.

404
00:18:43,199 --> 00:18:43,880
Look, look, look.

405
00:18:44,079 --> 00:18:45,119
It's really hydrating.

406
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:45,839
Isn't it?

407
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:46,760
Isn't it?

408
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,560
This one will definitely work great.

409
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:50,520
You're a grown man,

410
00:18:50,719 --> 00:18:51,719
how do you know so much about this?

411
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:52,920
Me?

412
00:18:53,599 --> 00:18:54,520
If I didn't know about this,

413
00:18:54,839 --> 00:18:56,680
how could I connect with women?

414
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:00,599
It smells pretty good.

415
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,760
Is that the scent of your hand cream?

416
00:19:04,439 --> 00:19:05,040
Look,

417
00:19:05,319 --> 00:19:05,760
from now on,

418
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:06,479
just use this one.

419
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:07,839
Let me smell it again.

420
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:10,239
It smells amazing.

421
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:11,800
Does it?

422
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:12,640
Let me smell it too.

423
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:13,599
It does smell good.

424
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:16,079
President Gu.

425
00:19:19,479 --> 00:19:20,560
The calm before the storm.

426
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:21,520
What are you talking about?

427
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:23,479
President Gu,

428
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:24,920
do you want some coffee?

429
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:25,920
I'll go make you some.

430
00:19:39,479 --> 00:19:40,040
What's wrong?

431
00:19:42,319 --> 00:19:43,920
You're not even as handsome as me.

432
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:48,800
What do you mean?

433
00:19:50,479 --> 00:19:52,160
Lin Jiaqi's poker face...

434
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,719
Why is she all smiles when she sees you?

435
00:19:55,959 --> 00:19:56,680
Do you have a secret?

436
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,359
A secret?

437
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:01,640
No.

438
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,319
Lin Jiaqi...

439
00:20:03,839 --> 00:20:05,119
doesn't have a poker face.

440
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:06,920
She doesn't?

441
00:20:07,599 --> 00:20:08,880
Every time I get close to her,

442
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,439
I feel freezing cold all over.

443
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:11,319
Let me tell you.

444
00:20:11,439 --> 00:20:12,479
Do you know what Lin Jiaqi's...

445
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:14,079
old nickname used to be?

446
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,520
Smiling Angel.

447
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,920
Smiling Angel?

448
00:20:17,199 --> 00:20:19,119
She smiled at every colleague she met.

449
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:20,439
Smiled?

450
00:20:21,439 --> 00:20:22,680
Her, a Smiling Angel?

451
00:20:23,079 --> 00:20:24,599
I think she's Miss Cold Front.

452
00:20:26,119 --> 00:20:26,599
No.

453
00:20:26,959 --> 00:20:27,560
Boss.

454
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:28,920
If I may be so bold,

455
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:29,680
I think

456
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:31,119
you've been a bit...

457
00:20:32,359 --> 00:20:32,760
thick-skinned lately.

458
00:20:34,079 --> 00:20:34,479
Look,

459
00:20:34,959 --> 00:20:36,439
how do you treat Lin Jiaqi?

460
00:20:36,439 --> 00:20:37,719
Don't you know it yourself?

461
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:38,959
I treat her very well.

462
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,400
Didn't I even help her get reinstated?

463
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:42,400
Right.

464
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:43,400
First, you make her lose her job,

465
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,079
and then you get her reinstated.

466
00:20:44,439 --> 00:20:44,880
Right?

467
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:47,119
I swear I'll beat you to death with this keyboard.

468
00:20:47,119 --> 00:20:48,000
No, no, no.

469
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,000
Put it down, put it down.

470
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:50,839
Boss,

471
00:20:51,239 --> 00:20:52,280
let me tell you the truth.

472
00:20:52,839 --> 00:20:53,800
This woman...

473
00:20:54,079 --> 00:20:55,760
won't let go of her anger that easily.

474
00:20:57,719 --> 00:20:59,239
Do you know why?

475
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,760
It's because she doesn't trust you.

476
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:02,839
She doesn't trust you at all.

477
00:21:03,119 --> 00:21:03,920
The moment she sees you,

478
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:04,599
she wonders

479
00:21:04,599 --> 00:21:06,119
what bad thing you'll do to her next.

480
00:21:06,959 --> 00:21:07,520
Towards you,

481
00:21:08,119 --> 00:21:08,719
in her heart,

482
00:21:09,199 --> 00:21:11,000
she can never let her guard down.

483
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,560
But what can I do?

484
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:14,280
I can't just walk into her heart

485
00:21:14,839 --> 00:21:15,839
and lower her defenses for her, can I?

486
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:18,760
Your emotional intelligence...

487
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:21,880
is really worrying.

488
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,359
You need to show your sincerity

489
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,359
and let her truly feel your friendliness.

490
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:30,560
Make her feel

491
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,160
that you really want to get along with her.

492
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,920
As long as she figures it out herself,

493
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:35,680
this matter will be settled.

494
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,800
Then how should I show my sincerity?

495
00:21:44,439 --> 00:21:45,040
Give her gifts.

496
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:46,599
Girls

497
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:48,000
like bags,

498
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:48,839
shoes, and stuff like that.

499
00:21:49,319 --> 00:21:49,719
Oh, right.

500
00:21:50,239 --> 00:21:50,920
You have to buy expensive ones.

501
00:21:51,359 --> 00:21:53,199
The heavier the gift, the deeper the affection.
